result.name: 壽司芳 Sushiyoshi

reviews.text:
I really enjoyed my meal here and I recommend trying if you are looking to to treat yourself to some tasty and phenomenal food. The service here is also really great and the staff take time to explain the food they are serving. You have your choice of omakase sets where the chef chooses the sushi to be served.

Food: 4.75 stars
Service: 4.5 stars
Environment: 4.25 stars
Overall:4.5 stars

 I came here for lunch and had the 9 sushi set and sort of wished I opted for the 12 piece set.  The set comes with 9 nigiri sushi, a roll, soup, and dessert. All the sushi here was really good and I enjoyed everything they served me. I tried some cuts of fish that I never had before like mantis shrimp and flounder.  The toro maki i had was probably my favorite. The maki was filled with three types of toro and a hint of green onion. I wish I could have had four more of these rolls.
Extremely fresh ingredients and creative dishes, loved the mixture of flavours and the friendly and funny chef. One of the favourites to be added to anyone’s list of best omakase.

Yummy and creative sushi with nice selection of sake
Definitely worth a try
Innovative sushi unlike others. Well balance between creativity and tradition.

🇭🇰✍🏻This Michelin two-starred Sushiyoshi from Osaka has truly suprised me with the unexpected flavor and textures. Chef Hiroki has successfully infused japanese tradition into every dish. Overall, a great omakase meal! 
°°°HK$987 pp°°°

reviews.text: If you want an all out decadent Omakase experience that will blow your mind and your wallet this is the place. It’s expensive but amazing. Fresh and rare fish, and a lot of it!

I really enjoyed my meal here and I recommend trying if you are looking to to treat yourself to some tasty and phenomenal food. The service here is also really great and the staff take time to explain the food they are serving. You have your choice of omakase sets where the chef chooses the sushi to be served.

Food: 4.75 stars
Service: 4.5 stars
Environment: 4.25 stars
Overall:4.5 stars

All the sushi here was really good and I enjoyed everything they served me. I tried some cuts of fish that I never had before like mantis shrimp and flounder.  The toro maki i had was probably my favorite. The maki was filled with three types of toro and a hint of green onion. I wish I could have had four more of these rolls.
Amazing food and one of the best valued omakase in Hong Kong

Amazing food! Staffs are professional, friendly and patient. 
Booked for 9 people and they reserve us a room!
Will def come again soon !
